This model will incorporate reference dependence by comparing the offered share to a reference point based on a simple expectation of fairness, adjusted by the trial type. The trial type will act as a contextual cue shifting the reference point. The second learnable parameter will capture the overall sensitivity to deviations from this adjusted reference point.


This model will predict the utility (U_accept) of accepting an offer by a responder in the bargaining game.  The model considers both self-interest (the monetary gain from accepting the offer, `split_self`) and a deviation from a fairness reference point.


